<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-420-955  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 420 955.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 10 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>McDonnell Douglas field service becomes Novadyne Computer Systems.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   McDonnell Douglas Field Service Co. (acquisitions and mergers)Novadyne Computer Systems Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     Securities TransferChief Executive OfficersManagementComputer industryAcquisition.andO;Person:    Novak, Bert (management).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MCDONNELL DOUGLAS FIELD SERVICE BECOMES NOVADYNE COMPUTER SYSTEMS SANTA ANA,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990 JUL 2 (NB) -- McDonnell Douglas Field Services hasbecome Novadyne Computer Systems as the result of a management buy-out headedby Bert Novak, president and CEO.andM;The company has assumed all sales and marketing responsibility for McDonnellDouglas Computers Systems products sold through dealers and VARs (value addedresellers) in North America.andP;  In addition Novadyne Computer Systems productsand services are marketed nationwide to companies in all types of businessesincluding retailing, transportation, distribution, communications, healthcare, educational organizations and federal and local governments.andM;Novadyne will also continue to provide services to end-users OEMs (originalequipment manufacturers), VARs and dealers delivering on-site servicesdesigned to meet specific user requirements with varying levels of responseand coverage hours.andP;  The company will also maintain depot repair services.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900706/Press Contact: Pat Dwight, Novadyne ComputerSystems, 714-566-4965)</TEXT></DOC>